<HEADLINE>
<P>
HARVEY HART; CANADIAN FILM, TV DIRECTOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TORONTO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Canadian film maker Harvey Hart, who directed episodes of "Columbo" and 
television miniseries, including "East of Eden," died of a heart attack Nov. 21 
at the age of 61. 
</P>
<P>
Hart, a pioneer director with CBC-TV, won a Golden Globe Award for "East of 
Eden," an adaptation of the John Steinbeck novel. 
</P>
<P>
His Canadian movies included "Fortune and Men's Eyes" and his U.S. work 
included the pilots for the series "Judd for the Defense" and "The Young 
Lawyers." 
</P>
<P>
Producer Victor Solnicki, who developed several projects with Hart, said the 
Toronto-born film maker "was proudest of his work during the golden years of 
CBC-TV drama." 
</P>
</TEXT>
