<HEADLINE>
<P>
GARDENA GIRLS WIN TENNIS TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG GONZALEZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gardena High won its second consecutive City Section 3-A girls tennis title 
Tuesday by defeating Franklin, 4-3, at the Racket Center in Studio City. 
</P>
<P>
Gardena finished the year 18-0. 
</P>
<P>
Senior Julie Oshiro beat her opponent 6-0, 6-1, to lead a singles sweep by 
Gardena. Oshiro is seeded No. 1 in the City individual playoffs, which combines 
4-A and 3-A. 
</P>
<P>
"We expected to sweep the singles," Coach Daron Andrade said. "That's what gave 
us the victory." 
</P>
<P>
Sophomore Mindy Watanabe and juniors Tiffany Kuwahara and Chris Ann Yamamoto 
completed the singles sweep for the Mohicans in the best-of-three matches. 
</P>
<P>
"We have worked so hard," Andrade said. "We've had a great year." GREG GONZALEZ 
</P>
</TEXT>
