<HEADLINE>
<P>
VOTERS LEAGUE SPONSORS HIGHER EDUCATION MEETING IN VENTURA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The League of Women Voters will sponsor a meeting Saturday addressing questions 
related to the need for higher education in Ventura County. The meeting, 
consisting of a panel of six speakers, will last from 10 a.m. to noon at 
Community Presbyterian Church, 115 Lincoln Drive, in Ventura. 
</P>
<P>
Speakers will include Russ Baggerly, a local environmentalist; economist Dick 
Felton; Michael Gonzalez, a counselor at Santa Paula High School; Ron Komers, 
personnel director for Ventura County; Elise Schneider, president of Oxnard 
College, and a representative from Cal State Northridge's Ventura Center. 
</P>
<P>
The meeting is part of an ongoing study of the higher-education issue by the 
league. The study does not deal with selection of a Ventura County site for a 
California State University, according to a league spokeswoman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
