<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Italy's Alberto Tomba won the second slalom of the World Cup skiing season by 
1.73 seconds at Waterville Valley, N.H. 
</P>
<P>
Tomba easily won both heats in times of 57.96 and 58.28 for a combined clocking 
of 1 minute 56.24 seconds. 
</P>
<P>
Pirmin Zurbriggen of Switzerland finished second in both runs with a 1:57.97 
total. Ole Christian Furuseth of Norway, who won last week's giant slalom at 
Park City, Utah, was fourth in 1:58.59. 
</P>
<P>
Felix McGrath of Hanover, N.H., placed eighth as the only U.S. finisher. 
</P>
