COACH: Dennis King, 2nd season 
</P>
<P>
LAST SEASON: 3-14; 3rd in league, 2-8 
</P>
<P>
PLAYERS TO WATCH: Three starters from a team that finished a game out of the 
cellar last season. King, however, has reason to hope for more this year. The 
returnees are a big reason: 6-0 senior forward Kenyon Wright (11.6 points) 
"shoots pretty well," according to King, and is joined in the frontcourt by 
junior Lodis Woodmore, a 6-2 forward. Joining that duo is senior Jesse Wallace 
(9.1 points, 7.4 rebounds), the quarterback of the football team and a swingman 
who is "not starting yet, but will soon," according to King. The coach likes 
