<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: POLICE CORNER SUSPECTED DRUG DEALER IN 
CLOSET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A suspected drug dealer wanted on federal narcotics charges and in the 
attempted murder of a police officer was captured in South Los Angeles on 
Wednesday after authorities cornered him in a closet, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Ricky Donnell Ross, 25, was also being sought for skipping $5-million bail on 
Texas cocaine trafficking charges, Los Angeles Police Sgt. Lon Salzman said. 
</P>
<P>
Ross, a former Crip gang member known as "Freeway Rick" because he owned a 
motel near the Harbor Freeway, is also wanted by the Drug Enforcement 
Administration on federal cocaine charges, police said. 
