<P>
RAIDERS' ALLEN RETURNS TO PRACTICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARK HEISLER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Marcus Allen returned to practice Wednesday, which means that the Raiders will 
activate him this week against the Denver Broncos or next week against the St. 
Louis Cardinals. 
</P>
<P>
At what position? 
</P>
<P>
"Marcus is a halfback," Coach Art Shell said, smiling. 
</P>
<P>
Allen has said he doesn't want to play fullback alongside Bo Jackson any 
longer. The question is, how much will Allen play after partially tearing a 
ligament in his right knee and sitting out the last seven games? 
</P>
<P>
And at 29, his $1.1-million contract expiring, will Al Davis sign him again? 
</P>
<P>
Significantly, Jackson, who has been increasingly banged up the last two weeks, 
went on the injury list. He is listed as probable with a bruised knee. Jackson 
has been held to 54 and 64 yards the last two games. 
</P>
<P>
Also returning to practice was receiver Sam Graddy. To make room, the Raiders 
waived running back Derrick Gainer and safety Derrick Crudup off their 
developmental squad. MARK HEISLER 
</P>
</TEXT>
