<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: NEWPORT BEACH; 
</P>
<P>
BALBOA ISLAND FERRY FARES GO UP A NICKEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beginning Friday, it will cost an extra nickel to ride the Balboa Island Ferry. 
</P>
<P>
Foot passengers will now be charged 25 cents, and the fee for a driver and a 
car will go up to 65 cents. Children's fares remain 10 cents, and those under 5 
ride for free. 
</P>
<P>
According to ferry officials, this is the first increase in six years and will 
help meet the high cost of operating the ferry, which includes fuel, upkeep and 
rent. 
</P>
<P>
There are also plans to eventually replace the 30-year-old ferries with new 
ones, officials said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
