FOR THE RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Catalina newspaper -- A Nov. 26 story on the Catalina Islander newspaper 
incorrectly identified the owner of the island. The Wrigley family, through the 
Santa Catalina Island Co., deeded title to about 86% of the island to the 
nonprofit Catalina Conservancy in 1975. The island company owns about 
two-thirds of the land in Avalon and about 20% of the city's buildings. 
</P>
