<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE'S HOLMES &amp; NARVER WINS $137-MILLION MIDEAST CONTRACTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN O'DELL, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ORANGE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Holmes &amp; Narver Services Inc. announced that it has been awarded contracts 
in Egypt and Saudi Arabia worth a total $137 million. 
</P>
<P>
The largest of the new contracts is a $66-million, three-year renewal of an 
existing contract for maintenance and operation of a large power plant and 
water desalination facility in Saudi Arabia. 
</P>
<P>
Holmes &amp; Narver Services also won a four-year, $43.5-million extension of 
its contract for logistical support of the Egyptian Sinai bases and outposts of 
the Multinational Force and Observers -- the peacekeeping force established in 
the 1979 Israeli-Egyptian peace treaty. 
</P>
<P>
Under that agreement, the company and its joint operating partner, CARE 
Services of Cairo, operate and maintain living quarters, community facilities, 
communications equipment and roads at two large base camps and 24 observation 
posts. 
</P>
<P>
The third contract, also granted jointly to Holmes &amp; Narver Services and 
CARE Services, is a $28-million agreement for maintenance of aircraft and 
aircraft weapons systems supplied to Egypt by the U.S. Air Force. 
</P>
<P>
The pact, which also calls for Holmes &amp; Narver to train Egyptian personnel 
to maintain the equipment, is for three years with options for two successive 
one-year renewals. 
</P>
<P>
Holmes &amp; Narver Services is a subsidiary of Holmes &amp; Narver Inc., a 
major engineering, design and construction project management firm. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
HOLMES AND NARVER SERVICES INC; CONTRACTS; UNITED STATES -- FOREIGN RELATIONS 
-- EGYPT; UNITED STATES -- FOREIGN RELATIONS -- SAUDI ARABIA; CARE SERVICES 
(COMPANY) 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
