105 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: RETAIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Mary Ann Galante, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Buy the Way: South Coast Plaza has just introduced a new incentive for shoppers 
to part with their money. 
</P>
<P>
Customers can now sign up for a Visa card issued through Security Pacific 
National Bank in conjunction with the mall that entitles them to special 
privileges -- for a fee. 
</P>
<P>
These privileges include advance notice of store openings, invitations to mall 
events such as fashion shows and free use of the mall's package claim service. 
</P>
<P>
The annual cost for the card is $25 (the charge for a conventional Visa card 
from the bank is $18), and it is subject to the usual 19.8% annual percentage 
rate on the outstanding balance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
