<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE EFFECTS OF MONO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DR. NEIL SOLOMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Question: Why does a person who has had mono have to be careful about taking 
part in athletics? Wouldn't exercise help speed up his recovery? Yet doctors 
discourage this. 
</P>
<P>
Answer: Patients with infectious mononucleosis have an enlarged spleen, which 
may be subject to rupture. Therefore, they should not take part in contact 
sports until the spleen has been returned to normal. 
</P>
<P>
For Carleton, Lexington, Ky.: Cocaine use is reported to be associated with the 
development of migraine-type headaches. 
</P>
</TEXT>
