DEPUTIES SEIZE 45 GUNS, ARREST 6 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Sheriff's Department anti-gang unit investigating a series of killings and 
extortions seized 45 assault weapons and arrested six people today in the 
Firestone Park area. 
</P>
<P>
Deputies with the Operation Safe Streets anti-gang squad investigating a series 
of drive-by shootings beginning last April made the arrests, Deputy Dean 
Scoville said. He said six gang members were arrested on charges of possessing 
illegal weapons -- including AR-15, AK-47 and Tec-9 assault rifles -- and that 
other charges may be added. 
