<P>
MAIL VAN KILLS VALLEY PEDESTRIAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Van Nuys pedestrian was struck and fatally injured by a U.S. Postal Service 
van when he walked in front of it, Los Angeles police said. 
</P>
<P>
Gerald Cuba, 56, of Van Nuys was pronounced dead at Valley Presbyterian 
Hospital shortly after the 7 p.m. accident Wednesday at Sepulveda Boulevard and 
Gilmore Street, Officer Ed Burns said. 
</P>
<P>
The van's driver, a Postal Service employee whose name was not released, was 
not cited, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Burns said the victim was trying to cross Sepulveda at Gilmore Street, where 
there is no marked crosswalk. A witness told police that Cuba stepped into the 
street without looking and was immediately struck by the van, which was 
northbound on Sepulveda at about 30 m.p.h., Burns said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
