<P>
NADIA HINTED AT U.S. EMBASSY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BUDAPEST, Hungary 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nadia Comaneci, the Olympic gymnastics champion who defected from her native 
Romania, may be at the U.S. Embassy in Switzerland, her coach said today. 
</P>
<P>
Embassy officials, however, denied she was there, adding another twist to the 
mystery surrounding the 1976 Olympic champion, who crossed the border into 
Hungary in the pre-dawn hours Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
"As far as I know, she is probably in the U.S. Embassy in Bern," Bela Karolyi 
told the Associated Press in a telephone interview from Stuttgart, West 
Germany, where he is coaching an American women's gymnastics team. 
</P>
<P>
"She is waiting to get some travel papers," said Karolyi. 
</P>
