<P>
GOSS BROTHERS SETTLE LIBEL SUIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LONDON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Luke and Matt Goss of the Bros pop band settled a libel lawsuit Wednesday with 
a newspaper they claimed had suggested that they took heroin. 
</P>
<P>
The People, a tabloid weekly, agreed to pay the 21-year-old twins a six-figure 
sum and publish an apology in next Sunday's paper, prosecutor Richard Hartley 
said. Hartley said the exact amount would not be disclosed, but six figures in 
British pounds is the equivalent of at least $160,000. The brothers, avid 
campaigners against drugs, testified at a libel hearing that articles in the 
newspaper in September, 1988, spoiled their "squeaky clean" image in the eyes 
of their mainly teen-age fans. 
