<P>
NAMES IN THE NEWS; 
</P>
<P>
FOXX MADE MILLIONS, LOST MORE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LAS VEGAS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Comedian Red Foxx once made $4 million a year but lost the money in lawsuits 
and broken deals and because he failed to heed the IRS, according to voluminous 
records in U.S. Bankruptcy Court. 
</P>
<P>
The IRS stepped in Tuesday and raided Foxx's home in Las Vegas, seizing his 
property -- including furniture, cars and jewelry he was wearing -- for failure 
to pay $755,166 in taxes. 
</P>
<P>
Foxx was left with an empty house, which the government says it will sell if he 
doesn't settle the tax debt in 30 to 45 days. 
</P>
<P>
Foxx was one of the top-paid performers in the United States in the 1970s. He 
currently works as a comedian at the Hacienda Hotel on the Las Vegas Strip, 
earning $20,000 a week. He said Tuesday the $20,000 has gone to the IRS the 
past several weeks. 
</P>
<P>
His manager, Prince Spencer, said Foxx was paid $500,000 for his role in the 
current film "Harlem Nights." Foxx vowed to bounce back from Tuesday's seizure. 
</P>
<P>
"I'll make it," he promised. "I got good friends." 
</P>
<P>
The $755,166 Foxx owes the IRS does not include interest and penalties. Court 
records show Foxx also owes state taxes in California and New Jersey. 
</P>
</TEXT>
