<P>
BROKEN FINGERS TAKE WIECHE OUT OF SLALOM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WATERVILLE VALLEY, N.H. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kyle Wieche, the top giant slalom racer on the U.S. ski team, broke two fingers 
on his left hand today and will be out for at least one month. 
</P>
<P>
Wieche, 22, of Farmington, Conn., fell during pre-race training for today's 
World Cup giant slalom at Waterville. He is expected to miss at least three 
more races. 
</P>
