Photo, Post-Turkey Trot to the Shopping Mall Begins: With Thanksgiving out of 
the way, shoppers looked ahead to December and the holidays. At Montclair 
Plaza, they lined the aisles, hunting for bargains and gifts for friends and 
relatives. Santa dropped by just in time for Karina Goderske, 3, to present her 
wish list and have her picture taken. At Santa Anita Fashion Park in Arcadia, 
shoppers could escape the yuletide atmosphere and divert their attention to a 
32-by 48-foot sand sculpture of a European village and castles. About 180 tons 
of sand was brought for the sculpture, which will be on exhibit through 
mid-January. Irfan Khan / Los Angeles Times 
